Terrie Waddell https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Terrie_Waddell 0 Terrie Waddell is a former Australian actress, and production manager best known for her role as Lisa Mullins in the television series Prisoner. She replaced Nicki Paull, who left the role due to an illness. Waddell remained with the series until its final episode in 1986. She subsequently moved away from acting to become a lecturer in media studies at La Trobe University.
